## Summary

This PR builds on the GLPI 11 migration started in v2.1.0 (by @loulouontop 
and @babydunet) and contributes the following:

---

## Bug Fixes

### 🔴 Critical: plugin reinstall wiped all category configuration
`init()` called `TRUNCATE` unconditionally on every install/upgrade, 
silently resetting all `is_active` settings to 0.  
Replaced with idempotent `syncCategories()` — inserts missing rows, 
removes orphaned ones, never touches existing configuration.

### 🔴 Critical: first ticket never assigned (first assignment bug)
`getLastAssignmentIndex()` returned `false` when `rr_groups` had no 
row yet (first ever ticket for a group). The handler interpreted `false` 
as "category disabled" and skipped assignment entirely.  
Fixed by distinguishing `false` (disabled) from `null` (first assignment 
→ start at index 0).

### 🟡 Bug: redundant `item_add` Ticket hook
The `item_add` hook for Ticket was registered but its callback was a 
no-op after the GLPI 11 migration. Removed to avoid confusion.

### 🟡 Bug: N+1 queries in `getAll()`
Config page fired one query per category + one per group + one per member 
count. Replaced with a single LEFT JOIN + one bulk raw COUNT query.

### 🟡 Bug: `COUNT(id)` broken via GLPI ORM
GLPI's `DB->request()` backticks every SELECT element, converting 
`COUNT(id) AS cnt` into invalid SQL. Fixed using `DB->doQuery()` directly 
for that query.

### 🟡 Bug: CRLF line endings in `TicketHookHandler.class.php`
Normalized to LF, consistent with the rest of the project.

